## Source Tagging Protocol

Every piece of information retrieved MUST be tagged with its source:

- **[DevDocs]** — Official API/library reference from DevDocs
- **[Stack Exchange]** — Community Q&A from Stack Exchange via ZIM
- **[man page]** — System manual pages for CLI tools and POSIX utilities
- **[NixOS]** — NixOS/Nix configuration options and package metadata
- **[Web]** — Web-fetched documentation via Context7

## Degradation Rules

1. Try sources in priority order (1 through 5)
2. If a source is unavailable or returns no results, move to the next
3. If a source returns partial results, note this and supplement from the next source
4. Always prefer local/offline sources over web when both have the answer
5. If no local source has the answer, use [Web] fallback

## Response Format

1. State which source(s) you consulted
2. Tag each piece of information with its source tag
3. If you had to fall back to a lower-priority source, explain why
4. Synthesize information from multiple sources when they complement each other
